subfields.a: Review of NOAA's Marine Operations Center-Pacific lease decision, 2010.
Marine Operations Center, Pacific website, viewed Feb. 7, 2013

The NOAA Marine Operations Center-Pacific (MOC-P) serves as a homeport for four NOAA research and survey ships and provides administrative, engineering, maintenance and logistical support for NOAA's Pacific fleet. The facility, which NOAA leases from the Port of Newport, includes 40,852 square feet of office and warehouse space, a 1,300-foot-long pier, and a small boat dock. The main buildings are built to Leadership in Energy and Environmental Design standards for environmentally sustainable construction. NOAA signed a 20-year lease with the Port of Newport in August 2009 following a competitive lease award process.
